# --- AI SEO Toolkit (Prisma + PostgreSQL + OpenRouter) ---
#
# Vercel: default build is `npm run build` (Next only) — migrations are NOT run on Vercel
# unless you set a custom Build Command (see below). This avoids deploy failures when
# DATABASE_URL/DIRECT_URL are wrong (P1013) or passwords need URL-encoding.
#
# Apply schema to Supabase once, from your laptop (with both URLs in `.env`):
#   npm run db:deploy
# Or paste `prisma/migrations/*/migration.sql` into Supabase → SQL Editor → Run.
#
# Optional — run migrations on every Vercel build (only after env vars are verified):
#   Vercel → Project → Settings → General → Build Command:
#   npm run build:with-migrate
#
# Supabase (two URLs — both required for Prisma CLI and for build:with-migrate):
#
# MUST start with postgresql:// or postgres:// — NOT https:// (the Supabase dashboard “Project URL” is wrong).
# In Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables: paste the value only — no surrounding "quotes".
#
# If the password contains @ : / # ? % etc., URL-encode them (e.g. @ → %40) or change the DB password in Supabase.
#
# 1) DATABASE_URL — Transaction pooler (port 6543) for the running app.
#    Supabase → Project Settings → Database → Connect → Transaction pooler → URI.
#    Append query params for Prisma + SSL, e.g.:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.PROJECT_REF:YOUR_PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&connection_limit=1&sslmode=require
#
# 2) DIRECT_URL — Direct connection for migrations (host db.PROJECT_REF.supabase.co, user often `postgres`).
# DIRECT_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@db.PROJECT_REF.supabase.co:5432/postgres?sslmode=require
#
# Other providers (Neon, etc.): use their pooled URL for DATABASE_URL and direct for DIRECT_URL if they document it.
#
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# Optional: OpenRouter model (default: mistralai/mistral-7b-instruct:free)
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=mistralai/mistral-7b-instruct:free

# --- Blog CMS (NextAuth + email/password) — /blogs, /blog-create ---
#
# Production (Vercel): REQUIRED — missing these causes /auth/error?error=Configuration
# NEXTAUTH_URL=https://rankflowhq.com
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET=<output of: openssl rand -base64 32>
# Also set BLOG_ADMIN_EMAIL, BLOG_ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH (or BLOG_ADMIN_PASSWORD) on Vercel.
#
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
# Only this email may sign in to /blog-create
BLOG_ADMIN_EMAIL=lariyaharsh88@gmail.com
# Password: use bcrypt hash (recommended). Default below matches generated password — CHANGE in production.
# Plain password (dev only): RfHQ-2026-Blog!mK9xQ7wZ
# To generate a new hash: node -e "console.log(require('bcryptjs').hashSync('YOUR_PASSWORD',10))"
BLOG_ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=$2b$10$0OYH0yuX0QGFZh6hGyUYT.sVJkBlMBwvRTEfn9SJ1TxpdWp7mQLWi
# Optional: plain password instead of hash (not recommended for production)
# BLOG_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Public URL for canonical links, Open Graph, sitemap, and robots (no trailing slash).
# Required in production for correct SEO URLs.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.example.com
# Use a full URL with https:// (or host only, e.g. www.example.com — https is assumed). Invalid values are ignored.

# Optional: Google Search Console HTML tag verification value only (not the full tag).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=...

# Optional: Google Analytics 4 Measurement ID (layout defaults to G-19XWBZXT88 if unset).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-19XWBZXT88

# Optional: AdSense client (ca-pub-…) — layout defaults to your publisher ID if unset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_CLIENT_ID=ca-pub-7494206891190273
#
# Display ad unit slot IDs (numeric, from AdSense → Ads → By ad unit). Create one unit per
# placement, then paste each ID. Leave unset to hide that slot until units are ready.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_SLOT_HOME_TOP=1234567890
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_SLOT_FOOTER=1234567890
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_SLOT_TOOL_INLINE=1234567890

# Used for the article pipeline, outlines, and the “Guide” section at the bottom of each tool page.
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_key_here
# Optional: preferred text model (tried first; others still used on fallback). Do not use *-tts or
# audio-only IDs (e.g. gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts) — they cannot return text for the pipeline.
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash
#
# Education news (/education-news): after each sitemap sync, rows **newly inserted** in that sync
# are auto-repurposed with Gemini (no button). Capped per sync for time/cost.
# EDUCATION_NEWS_AUTO_REPURPOSE=false   # omit or true to enable when GEMINI_API_KEY is set
# EDUCATION_NEWS_AUTO_REPURPOSE_LIMIT=2   # max 1–5 new pending articles per sync (default 2)
#
# Google News sitemap at /news/sitemap.xml (news: namespace only; image blocks omitted). Each URL uses changefreq daily and priority 1.
# NEWS_SITEMAP_PUBLICATION_NAME=RankFlowHQ News
# NEWS_SITEMAP_LANGUAGE=en
# NEWS_SITEMAP_GENRES=PressRelease, Blog
# NEWS_SITEMAP_ARTICLE_IMAGE_URL_TEMPLATE=   # reserved; sitemap does not emit image:image until re-enabled with absolute https URLs
#
# News hero images (https://images.rankflowhq.com): after repurpose, a 1200×630 PNG is uploaded to
# Vercel Blob at `news/{slug}.png`. Point your subdomain CNAME at Blob (Vercel dashboard) and set:
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=   # Vercel → Storage → Blob → token (required for upload)
# IMAGES_CDN_BASE=https://images.rankflowhq.com   # optional; rewrites stored/sitemap URLs to this host
# (Host-only values like images.rankflowhq.com are normalized to https:// — required for valid sitemap image URLs.)
# Optional: HTTPS URL of exam/board logo for the /news featured OG template (left column). Override per article with DB `examLogoUrl`.
# NEWS_FEATURED_EXAM_LOGO_URL=https://…/exam-board-logo.png
#
# IndexNow — when a repurposed news article becomes `ready`, the server POSTs the article URL
# (and by default `/news/sitemap.xml`) to IndexNow (Bing, Yandex, Naver, etc.).
# Google does not support IndexNow; add your sitemap in Google Search Console for Google crawls.
# https://www.indexnow.org/documentation — create a key and host `INDEXNOW_KEY` as plain text at INDEXNOW_KEY_URL.
# INDEXNOW_KEY=
# INDEXNOW_KEY_URL=https://rankflowhq.com/your-key-filename.txt
# Optional: only submit the article URL, not the news sitemap (default is both).
# INDEXNOW_INCLUDE_NEWS_SITEMAP=false
#
# Telegram: optional channel alerts (text + “Read More” + hub link; no images). Create a bot with
# @BotFather, then add the bot as an administrator on each channel. Use the channel chat id
# (often -100…) — post once in the channel and read id from getUpdates, or use @getidsbot.
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456789:AA…
# TELEGRAM_BLOG_CHAT_ID=-100…   # sent when POST /api/blog creates a published post
# TELEGRAM_NEWS_CHAT_ID=-100…   # sent when repurposing finishes (status → ready)
# TELEGRAM_BLOG_HUB_BUTTON_TEXT=RankFlowHQ Blog    # optional; second button → /blogs
# TELEGRAM_NEWS_HUB_BUTTON_TEXT=RankFlowHQ News   # optional; second button → /news
# Site assistant (floating chat, DeepSeek — OpenAI-compatible API at api.deepseek.com)
# Get a key: https://platform.deepseek.com — server-only; never expose in client code.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# Optional: override API base (default https://api.deepseek.com/v1 → …/v1/chat/completions).
# DEEPSEEK_API_BASE=https://api.deepseek.com/v1
# Optional: default is deepseek-chat. Use deepseek-reasoner only if you accept slower, longer replies.
# DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-chat
# Optional: set to 0 or false to hide the chat bubble (e.g. until the key is set in production).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_CHAT=1

TAVILY_API_KEY=your_tavily_key_here
SERPER_API_KEY=your_serper_key_here

# Optional: OpenAI — only if you wire features that call OpenAI APIs (seo-enrich uses free Pollinations for images).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional: Google Search Console — enables “Fetch Search Console queries” in the UI.
# Enable “Google Search Console API” in Google Cloud for the same project as the service account.
#
# Recommended: service account (no OAuth). Create a service account, download JSON, paste the
# entire JSON as a single line in Vercel (or use a multiline env). Add the service account
# email in Search Console → Settings → Users and permissions (Full or Owner).
# GSC_SITE_URL must match the property string in Search Console exactly (www vs non-www,
# https, trailing slash, or sc-domain:example.com for domain properties).
# GSC_SITE_URL=https://www.example.com/
# GSC_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account","project_id":"...","private_key_id":"...","private_key":"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n","client_email":"...@....iam.gserviceaccount.com",...}
#
# Legacy: OAuth refresh token instead of service account.
# GSC_CLIENT_ID=
# GSC_CLIENT_SECRET=
# GSC_REFRESH_TOKEN=
